Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Pomona is the seventh largest city in Los Angeles County, with a population of over 151,000 residents, it boasts a progressive economy, business opportunity, and a strong workforce with attractive shopping, recreational, and real estate offering. Pomona has continued to experience rapid growth with homes still being built in the hilly area between Downtown and Diamond Bar.

Today, Phillips Ranch is nearly all residential while northern Pomona has seen some gentrification with additional housing units added and revamped streetscapes. Pomona is a vibrant community striving to provide a high quality of life for all of Pomona. Top employers in the city are Pomona Unified School District, Pomona Valley Hospital Medical Center, California State Polytechnic University, Pomona, Lanterman Developmental Center, City of Pomona, Casa Colina Rehabilitation Center, Verizon, County of Los Angeles Department ect..

Strong market fundamentals have kept vacancy low, allowing rents to increase significantly over the last seven years, averaging 3.1% annually. Moving forward, it is expected that retail fundamentals will remain strong due to demand outpacing supply, providing further rental growth.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
Anaheim is a city in Orange County, California, part of the Los Angeles metropolitan area. As of 2019 the city had a population of over 336,264, making it the most populated city in Orange County and the 10th-most populated city in California.

Anaheim is the second-largest city in Orange County in terms of land area and is known for being the home of the Disneyland Resort, the Anaheim Convention Center, and two major sports teams: the Anaheim Ducks ice hockey club and the Los Angeles Angels baseball team.

Located in the geographic center of Orange County, Anaheim is one of the most visited cities in the United States. Anaheim draws in visitors through its music venues, major theme parks, sports teams, and convention center. The city is working to move from away from being a simple tourist destination, however. In recent years, Anaheim has seen tremendous growth in its commercial sector, with new developments adding more retail, multifamily, and office to the area. One of the most prominent areas for development is known as the Platinum Triangle.

The Platinum Triangle is a neo-urban redevelopment district surrounding and including Angel Stadium, Honda Center and the Grove of Anaheim. The Platinum Triangle blends leading-edge business, high-salary employment, world class entertainment and residential neighborhoods, to create a unique opportunity in the heart of Orange County, offering immediate access to the rest of Southern California from three freeways and a major transit center.

This proximity to major thoroughfares and transit centers gives Anaheim’s residents access to the amenities of both Los Angeles and Orange County. Residents are exposed to top tier companies such as Tesla, Edison International, Molina Healthcare and more.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE is proud to present a new STNL Grocery Outlet (NASDAQ: “GO”), market capitalization of over USD $2.98B, trophy asset located in the heart of Anaheim, one of Orange County’s most established dense, infill trade areas.  This asset features unmatched visibility from the signalized hard corner, with over 270 feet of frontage on Lincoln Avenue, a major freeway exit.

The Los Angeles Fashion District is the hub of the L.A. fashion industry, featuring
more than 2,000 independently owned retail and wholesale business with apparel,
accessories and footwear. The district is also home to the lively Santee Alley, the largest selection of fabrics and notions in Southern California, and the L.A. Flower District, the largest flower market in the United States. However, retail shopping is an integral part of the district. The Fashion District is a bargain hunter’s paradise, with over 1,000 stores that sell to the general public at wholesale discounted prices. Shoppers can expect to find bargains of 30-70% off retail prices on apparel and accessories at stores, many of which are open 365 days a year. The district employs a ‘Clean & Safe Team’, easily recognized by their signature yellow uniform and on patrol 24-hours a day, seven days a week in order to maintain a positive public environment for visitors and the community alike.
